(54, '54', 1, 'Analysing Generical Moves in Pedagogical Sales Reply Emails', 'analysing generical moves in pedagogical sales reply emails', 'moves analysis, promotional genre, sales reply emails, written communication, corpus', 'This study aimed to investigate the generic features in the business emails written by the undergraduates of Universiti Malaysia Kelantan (UMK). Besides that, this study intended to propose a standard generic structure in writing a business email. The emails were gathered from the respondents\' assignment that comprised of two email-based questions; however, this study analysed the generic structure of sales reply emails. The emails were compared with Bhatia\'s promotional sales letter moves. The methodology of this study was computer-assisted corpus analysis (CACA) by Manvender (2011). The data were analysed using a genre-based technique by Bhatia (1993). The particular moves and steps in both types of texts were recognised and categorised individually. The rhetorical structure of sales reply emails consists of three major moves: introducing product, product details, offering incentives. Although the respondents showed similarities in their moves, there were some differences such as the number and content of the moves as well as the contextual patterns.', '<p>Askehave, I., &amp; Swales, J. M. (2001). Genre identification and communicative purpose: A problem and a possible solution. <em>Applied Linguistics</em>, <em>22</em>(2), 195&ndash;212.</p>\r\n<p>Bhatia, V. K. (1993). <em>Analysing Genre: Language Use in Professional Settings</em>. Pearson Education Limited (Vol. 19). https://doi.org/10.1016/0889-4906(95)90021-7</p>\r\n<p>Budge, S. B. (2006). <em>To deceive the receiver A genre analysis of the electronic variety of Nigerian scam letters</em>. (Online) Available from: http://www.diva-portal.org/smash/get/diva2:206940/FULLTEXT01.pdf</p>\r\n<p>Cheung, M. (2011). Sales promotion communication in Chinese and English: A thematic analysis. <em>Journal of Pragmatics</em>, <em>43</em>(4), 1061&ndash;1079</p>\r\n<p>Gimenez, J. C. (2006). Embedded business emails: Meeting new demands in international business communication. <em>English for Specific Purposes</em>, <em>25</em>(2), 154&ndash;172.</p>\r\n<p>Hanel, S., &amp; Cortes, V. (2010). Identifying moves and elements of persuasion in collection letters. <em>Revista de Lenguas Para Fines Espec&iacute;ficos</em>, <em>1127</em>(April), 83&ndash;108.</p>\r\n<p>Manvender Kaur. (2011). Syntax in a Business Context: A Learner Corpus Analysis. <em>ELT: Converging Evidence and Challenges</em>, (March). Available from https://www.jbe- platform.com/content/series/13880373?pageSize=100&amp;page=1</p>\r\n<p>Park, M. Y., Dillon, W. T., &amp; Mitchell, K. L. (1998). Korean Business Letters: Strategies for Effective Complaints in Cross-Cultural Communication. <em>The Journal of Business Communication</em>, <em>35</em>, 328&ndash;345.</p>\r\n<p>Sandelowski, M., Voils, C. I., &amp; Knafl, G. (2009). On quantitizing. <em>Journal of Mixed Methods Research</em>, <em>3</em>(3), 208&ndash;222. Swales, J. M. (1990). <em>The concept of discourse community</em>. <em>Cambridge University Press</em>. https://doi.org/10.4000/asp.4774</p>\r\n<p>Vergaro, C. (2004). Discourse strategies of Italian and English sales promotion letters. <em>English for Specific Purposes</em>, <em>23</em>(2), 181&ndash;207.</p>', 1, 'ArticleWorkflow/qa-publish', '', '2019-01-11 17:31:07', '2019-01-08 15:15:08', '2019-01-08 15:15:22', '2019-01-08 15:31:30', 91, 47, '', '', '2019-01-08 15:32:21', 0, '2019-01-08 15:56:08', 91, '2019-01-08 15:58:46', '', 4, 4, '', 91, '2019-01-08 15:59:42', 91, '2019-01-08 16:02:46', '', '2019-01-08 16:05:14', '', '', 91, '2019-01-08 16:06:53', 91, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 1, '', '', '2019-01-08 16:07:28', 91, '', 239, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', '', '2019-01-08 16:07:55', 91, '', '', '2019-01-08 16:13:07', 91, '', '2019/01619A/cameraready_1547