<em>British Journal of Health Psychology, 14</em>, 681-699.</p>\r\n<p>Wheeler, S., Yeomans, P. &amp; Wheeler, D. (2008). The good, the bad and the wiki: Evaluating student-generated content for collaborative learning. <em>British Journal of Educational Technology, 39 </em>(6), 987-995.</p>', 1, 'ArticleWorkflow/qa-publish', '', '2019-01-11 16:38:19', '2019-01-08 15:15:08', '2019-01-08 15:15:22', '2019-01-08 15:31:30', 91, 47, '', '', '2019-01-08 15:32:21', 0, '2019-01-08 15:56:08', 91, '2019-01-08 15:58:46', '', 4, 4, '', 91, '2019-01-08 15:59:42', 91, '2019-01-08 16:02:46', '', '2019-01-08 16:05:14', '', '', 91, '2019-01-08 16:06:53', 91, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 1, '', '', '2019-01-08 16:07:28', 91, '', 239, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', '', '2019-01-08 16:07:55', 91, '', '', '2019-01-08 16:13:07', 91, '', '2019/01619A/cameraready_15471958995c3855fb1d5f58.79861874.pdf', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2018-12-11 16:24:19', 47, 10, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', '01', 0, '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 1, 10, ' 10.17687/JEB.0602.01'),
(59, 'JEB.2018.06.02.028', 251, 'MODEL SADAQA HOUSE: MENYANTUNI KEBAJIKAN UMMAH', 'model sadaqa house: menyantuni kebajikan ummah', 'SADAQA HOUSE, VBI, Prestasi Perbankan Islam, Kewangan Sosial, Kebajikan', 'SADAQA HOUSE merupakan salah satu elemen dalam kewangan sosial yang menggunakan konsep sedekah di dalam sektor perbankan dan kewangan Islam. Idea SADAQA HOUSE tercetus daripada Dato? Dr. Abdul Halim Ismail, pemenang Anugerah Diraja Kewangan Islam tahun 2014, di mana beliau menekankan bahawa sektor kerajaan dan sektor swasta berperanan dalam mengumpulkan dana bagi disalurkan kepada golongan miskin dan yang memerlukan. Menurut beliau juga, sektor perbankan dan kewangan Islam perlu membangunkan produk atau perkhidmatan yang dapat membantu penyaluran dana tersebut. Walaubagaimanapun, berdasarkan pandangan beliau, sektor perbankan dan kewangan Islam semasa masih kurang memberi tumpuan dalam aspek ini. Kajian kebolehlaksanaan SADAQA HOUSE dalam kerangka perbankan yang telah dijalankan oleh Kolej Universiti Islam Antarabangsa Selangor (KUIS) dari tahun 2014 hingga 2018 mendapati hasilnya adalah positif dan ia boleh dilaksanakan sama ada sebagai perkhidmatan atau produk bank. Berdasarkan hasil kajian tersebut, Bank Islam Malaysia Berhad (BIMB) telah mengambil langkah proaktif sebagai bank pertama di Malaysia yang melaksanakan model SADAQA HOUSE. Hal ini selari dengan inisiatif baru Bank Negara Malaysia (BNM) yang memperkenalkan Pengantaraan Berasaskan Nilai (VBI). Bank Islam telah melancarkan produk SADAQA HOUSE pada Januari 2018 semasa Karnival Kewangan di Kedah. Model SADAQA HOUSE ini dipercayai dapat membantu dalam menyantuni kebajikan ummah. Walaubagaimanapun, masih belum terdapat kajian yang melihat sejauh mana pencapaian SADAQA HOUSE Bank Islam dalam menyantuni kebajikan ummah. Kajian ini akan menganalisa pencapaian SADAQA HOUSE Bank Islam sejak pelaksanaannya pada Januari 2018. Kajian ini akan menggunakan data sekunder dan juga temu bual strategik bersama pegawai-pegawai Bank Islam yang terlibat dalam projek SADAQA HOUSE. Hasil Kajian dijangka akan memberi kesan yang positif kepada ummah dan secara amnya kepada pembangunan negara.', '', 4, 'ArticleWorkflow/ha-correction', '2019/asrulhery@gmail.com/submission_15583529925ce294606d3783.31910340.doc', '2019-05-20 20:43:40', '2019-05-20 19:49:37', '2019-05-20 19:50:04', '2019-05-20 20:44:05', 91, 91, '2019/01258A/review_15583562205ce2a0fce40f06.57312740.pdf', '', '2019-05-20 20:54:12', 0, '2019-05-25 11:03:16', 69, '2019-05-29 12:34:26', 'I didn\'t check similarities, or initial assessment as the paper is in BM. EIC should check and recommend.', 4, 2, 'Totally agree with the second internal reviewer.', 55, '2019-05-30 06:59:39', 69, '2019-05-30 12:09:41', 'Dear Ms. LATIFA BIBI MUSAFAR HAMEED\r\n\r\nThis is to inform you that, after careful consideration, the editorial team has decided to reconsider your manuscript for publication, should you be prepared to incorporate major revisions. When preparing your revised manuscript, you are asked to carefully consider the reviewer comments, which are attached, and submit a list of responses to the comments.\r\n\r\nPlease amend your paper based on the comments. All amendment in the manuscript, please highlight (use Track Changes). Please prepare a separate document titled - Reply to Reviewer(s) comments. In that document, write down the (1) reviewer(s) comment, (2) Author(s) reply to reviewer(s) comment and (3) amendment in the Manuscript (What you added or deleted based on the comments) for Each Comment. Please note thatJEB will not consider your paper further if you do not follow the instructions properly as mentioned above.\r\n\r\nPlease send the amended version of your paper by 15thJuly 2019.\r\n\r\n\r\nEditorial Note: Please write the abstract in English and BM\r\n\r\nReview Note.\r\n1. The writing style is not coherent with the article style of writing\r\n2. The methodology part was not clearly stated, the author did not describe any tool/technique of analysis. Also not mentioned on the steps in the analysis\r\n3. The objectives of the study are too general and not represented/answered through the methodology- ambiguous\r\n4. Need for more extensively literature reviews\r\n5. Due to the insufficient material in supporting the methodology, the overall paper is not strong enough\r\n6. Abstract part- must contain the main objective, methodology, analysis and significant finding of the study\r\n7. VBI part was not extensively described in the paper. Need for details on VBI\r\n8. SADAQA HOUSE - why use capital letter?\r\n9. The problem statement is greatly in a false way - not stated \r\n10. The author supposedly can elaborate more on the steps/flows of both models in Sadaqa House', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', '', 0, '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, ''),
