(69, 'JEB.2019.07.01.008', 251, 'Intention to adopt electric vehicle using the theory of planned behavior model: Evidence from Jordan', 'intention to adopt electric vehicle using the theory of planned behavior model: evidence from jordan', 'Attitude towards adoption EV, Subjective norm, perceived behavioral control, adoption intention, electric vehicle EV.', 'Using the electric vehicles (EVs) is indispensable for the reduction in fossil fuels consumption which are the main cause of carbon emission. However, research investigating the intention to adopt electric vehicle from developing countries perspective is limited. To fill this gap, this study used TPB model to study the effect of Attitude towards adoption EV, Subjective norm, and Perceived behavioral control on Intention to adopt electric vehicle. The conceptual framework of the study hypothesized several relationships and for that the data was collected through a questionnaire from a sample of 250 individual in Jordan. Results show that Attitude towards adoption EV, Subjective norm, and Perceived behavioral control have a positive influence on EV adoption intention. The findings lead towards the important implications that will help understanding consumer behavior towards adoption of EVs.', '', 1, 'ArticleWorkflow/ha-correction', '2019/asrulhery@gmail.com/submission_15583665465ce2c9527c7cc6.95491786.docx', '2019-05-20 23:44:11', '2019-05-20 23:35:20', '2019-05-20 23:35:52', '2019-05-20 23:44:16', 91, 91, '2019/01258A/review_15583670515ce2cb4bca8d62.65791602.pdf', '', '2019-05-20 23:52:56', 0, '2019-06-11 14:05:56', 69, '2019-06-11 15:06:04', 'Recommend - Major Revision\r\n\r\nReviewer\'s Comments:\r\n\r\nThe topic is interesting to be explored. It addresses the intention of using electric vehicles which would help to reduce the pollution. However, literature review should be divided into four sections; 1) Theory of Planned Behavior, 2) Attitude, 3) Subjective Norm, and 4) Perceived Behavioral Control, or at least reflects comprehensively the variables. It is understandable that they are emphasized in theoretical framework and research hypothesis. Therefore, the structure of literature review and theoretical framework and research hypothesis should be revisited in order to have a better structure of literature review. Spelling error is found; transpiration instead of transportation. Grammar must be polished to ensure better understanding by the reader. References from year 2018 and 2019 should be included to allow up-to-date work.\r\n\r\n1. Abstract \r\n-the term of \"TPB model\" should be in full spelling (Theory of Perceived Behaviour Model).\r\n- the contribution/significant of the study is recommended to be added in the abstract.\r\n\r\n2. Introduction\r\n- several of the statements did not have citations.\r\n- recommended to explain the content of the study, which is the intention to adopt technology, followed by context which is the which is electric vehicles (EVs) with arguments on related studies been done by scholars, \r\n- spelling error \'overview of transportation in Jordan\'\r\n- it also should highlight the problem statement of this study.\r\n\r\n3. The literature review slightly not sufficient as it only discussed on the TPB model. \r\n\r\n4. Methodology\r\n-Paragraph 1 is recommended to rewrite. For example para 1, line 3 - \" As the study was aimed to examine the factors that influence the EVs behavioral intentions in Jordan\". The statement was incomplete and unclear as it also contradicted with objective mentioned in the abstract (abstract, line 4).\r\n- recommended to include how the sampling were selected (sampling technique)\r\n\r\n5. Result\r\n- a few of the tables presented split into another page. \r\n\r\n6. Discussion\r\n- Para 1, line 1-10 - the statement is repetitive with the abstract (line 1-10).\r\n- recommended to rewrite this section. \r\n\r\nThe article is highly recommended to submit to proof reader before submission. ', 3, 3, 'The article should be revised before continuing with the second review.', 55, '2019-06-12 08:40:45', 69, '2019-06-12 13:21:36', 'Dear Authors\r\n \r\nThis is to inform you that, after careful consideration, the editorial team has decided to reconsider for publication should you be prepared to incorporate Major revisions. When preparing your revised manuscript, you are asked to carefully consider the reviewer comments, which are attached, and submit a list of responses to the comments.\r\n \r\nPlease amend your paper based on the comments. Keep all your responses in a separate page (Example: Reviewer’s comment: xxxxxxx. Response to reviewer’s comment 1: xxxxxxxxxxxxx). Please mail me the amended manuscript and your response to the reviewer\'s comments in separate document.\r\n \r\nPlease send the amended version of your paper when ready.\r\n \r\nReviewer’s comments:\r\n\r\nThe topic is interesting to be explored. It addresses the intention of using electric vehicles which would help to reduce the pollution. However, literature review should be divided into four sections; 1) Theory of Planned Behavior, 2) Attitude, 3) Subjective Norm, and 4) Perceived Behavioral Control, or at least reflects comprehensively the variables. It is understandable that they are emphasized in theoretical framework and research hypothesis. Therefore, the structure of literature review and theoretical framework and research hypothesis should be revisited in order to have a better structure of literature review. Spelling error is found; transpiration instead of transportation. Grammar must be polished to ensure better understanding by the reader. References from year 2018 and 2019 should be included to allow up-to-date work.\r\n\r\n1. Abstract \r\n-the term of \"TPB model\" should be in full spelling (Theory of Perceived Behaviour Model).\r\n- the contribution/significant of the study is recommended to be added in the abstract.\r\n\r\n2. Introduction\r\n- several of the statements did not have citations.\r\n- recommended to explain the content of the study, which is the intention to adopt technology, followed by context which is the which is electric vehicles (EVs) with arguments on related studies been done by scholars, \r\n- spelling error \'overview of transportation in Jordan\'\r\n- it also should highlight the problem statement of this study.\r\n\r\n3. The literature review slightly not sufficient as it only discussed on the TPB model. \r\n\r\n4. Methodology\r\n-Paragraph 1 is recommended to rewrite. For example para 1, line 3 - \" As the study was aimed to examine the factors that influence the EVs behavioral intentions in Jordan\". The statement was incomplete and unclear as it also contradicted with objective mentioned in the abstract (abstract, line 4).\r\n- recommended to include how the sampling were selected (sampling technique)\r\n\r\n5. Result\r\n- a few of the tables presented split into another page. \r\n\r\n6. Discussion\r\n- Para 1, line 1-10 - the statement is repetitive with the abstract (line 1-10).\r\n- recommended to rewrite this section. \r\n\r\nThe article is highly recommended to submit to proof reader before submission.\r\n\r\n-- \r\nRegards\r\n\r\nEditorial Team\r\nJournal of Entrepreneurship and Business\r\n(http://fkp.umk.edu.my/jeb/)', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', '', 0, '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, ''),
(70, 'JEB.2019.07.01.009 ', 251, 'Exploring the Role of Education on the Entrepreneurial Motivations of Academic Spin-offs? Founders', 'exploring the role of education on the entrepreneurial motivations of academic spin-offs’ founders', 'academic spin-offs, human capital, entrepreneurial motivations, qualifications, founders, case study', 'Academic spin-offs are increasingly assuming a relevant role in the social and economic contexts. Despite this, there are a few studies that look at the specific role of human capital in these organizations. A contradictory dimension in human capital is the role of founder?s education, in which there are studies that demonstrate a relationship between the entrepreneurial motivation and education levels, and others studies that indicate that these two variables are uncorrelated. In this sense, this study seeks to explore and understand the reasons for these contradictory results by conducting case studies using in-depth interviews among six Portuguese academic spin-offs. The results of this study made it possible to perceive the low motivation of Ph.D. students to create new ventures, to explore the role of professional and technical courses, and to understand how the acquired knowledge in master business administration courses turns out to be little relevant for entrepreneurs.', '', 6, 'ArticleWorkflow/ha-correction', '2019/asrulhery@gmail.com/submission_15583667295ce2ca09a59934.89410103.docx', '2019-05-20 23:43:08', '2019-05-20 23:38:37', '2019-05-20 23:39:51', '2019-05-20 23:43:27', 91, 91, '2019/01258A/review_15583669885ce2cb0cdc2da9.04786008.pdf', '', '2019-05-20 23:52:34', 0, '2019-06-15 07:16:01', 69, '2019-06-16 10:45:57', '\r\n\r\nComments:\r\n\r\n# Should indicate the contradict discussion on education and entrepreneurial motivation since previous study indicates PhD level in need for high technology firm. \r\n# Should indicate the analysis technique in detail\r\n# the proposition for the results are not clear indicated\r\n\r\nThe study fails to show the overall picture of why this study is worth to be conducted. The language used is unclear and making it difficult to follow. I personally advice the author to seek for proofreader help to improve and readability of the text. The author need to rewrite the whole part of literature review and be more precise with their scope of study. In this study, the main focus is entrepreneur so the author need to be more specific. The author started well but he has missed out some important points that can strengthen the whole research in literature. Important elements in key papers should be expanded and clarified to ensure that readers understand exactly what the researchers studied. The objectives of this study does not really fit for the mode of methodology chosen for this study. The author should keep in mind that qualitative research is a reflective piece of work.', 4, 3, 'Based on the comments of the 2nd reviewer and the ME, the paper should be reviewed before sending for the second review.', 55, '2019-06-16 12:46:02', 69, '2019-06-16 13:00:31', 'Dear Dr. Fernando Almeida,\r\nThis is to inform you that after careful consideration, the editorial team has decided to reconsider for publication should you be prepared to incorporate Major revisions. When preparing your revised manuscript, you are asked to carefully consider the reviewer comments, which are attached, and submit a list of responses to the comments.\r\n \r\nPlease amend your paper based on the comments. Keep all your responses in a separate page (Example: Reviewer’s comment: xxxxxxx. Response to reviewer’s comment 1: xxxxxxxxxxxxx). Please mail me the amended manuscript and your response to the reviewer\'s comments in separate document.\r\n \r\nPlease send the amended version of your paper when ready.\r\n \r\nReviewer’s comments:\r\n\r\n# Should indicate the contradict discussion on education and entrepreneurial motivation since previous study indicates PhD level in need for high technology firm. \r\n# Should indicate the analysis technique in detail\r\n# the proposition for the results are not clear indicated\r\n\r\nThe study fails to show the overall picture of why this study is worth to be conducted. The language used is unclear and making it difficult to follow. I personally advice the author to seek for proofreader help to improve and readability of the text. The author need to rewrite the whole part of literature review and be more precise with their scope of study. In this study, the main focus is entrepreneur so the author need to be more specific. The author started well but he has missed out some important points that can strengthen the whole research in literature. Important elements in key papers should be expanded and clarified to ensure that readers understand exactly what the researchers studied. The objectives of this study does not really fit for the mode of methodology chosen for this study. The author should keep in mind that qualitative research is a reflective piece of work.\r\n', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', '', 0, '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, '');
