this factor with \"thus, perceived flood risk was one...\"\r\n\r\nPage 3: Data and methodology\r\nIt would be better if you can explain a little bit further on the sample - the area that has been selected. Is it coastal area? If so, need to be more careful as we all know that most of the people who lived there are categorized under \'lower middle income\". In this case, they were \"feel reluctant to insure their property due to premium and budget constraints (Aliagha et al., 2014). \r\nYou did mentioned \"Kota Bharu\" in the conclusion section so please explain it under data section. \r\n\r\nYou were also mentioned Protection Motivation Theory as to support your analysis (in page 5) but I cant see any discussion referring to that theory. You need more detail on the theory. \r\n\r\nThere are language and grammatical issue throughout that need careful checking.\r\n\r\nThe reference list is incomplete with reference in the text that are not in the list itself.\r\n(DID, 2007;2009)\r\n\r\n1. The author needs to add more literature in the study. No recent article is stated, only one.\r\n2. Repeatedly used the same literature in the study. Please avoid.\r\n3. The study needs to be precise, Kota Bharu only? Why used only 30 respondents? \r\n4. What is the motivation leads to this study? Please explain. \r\n', 3, 3, 'Need to review as recommended by the second reviewer before sending for the second review.', 55, '2019-06-12 08:43:01', 69, '2019-06-12 13:30:55', 'Att: Dear Dr. KESHMINDER SINGH JIT SINGH. Coordinator Research & Publication, Universiti Teknologi MARA\r\n\r\nPlease forward the email to authors and cc to us for the record.\r\n\r\nDear Azreen Roslan, Nurul Alysa Sofea Shaharuddin & Norliza Che Yahya\r\n \r\nThis is to inform you that, after careful consideration, the editorial team has decided to reconsider for publication should you be prepared to incorporate Major revisions. When preparing your revised manuscript, you are asked to carefully consider the reviewer comments, which are attached, and submit a list of responses to the comments.\r\n \r\nPlease amend your paper based on the comments. Keep all your responses in a separate page (Example: Reviewer’s comment: xxxxxxx. Response to reviewer’s comment 1: xxxxxxxxxxxxx). Please mail me the amended manuscript and your response to the reviewer\'s comments in separate document.\r\n \r\nPlease send the amended version of your paper when ready.\r\n \r\nReviewer’s comments:\r\n\r\nOverall the study was interesting. However, here are some comments that require your further action;\r\n\r\nPage 2: 2.3: Flood damage experience \r\nPerhaps, you wrongly concluded this factor with \"thus, perceived flood risk was one...\"\r\n\r\nPage 3: Data and methodology\r\nIt would be better if you can explain a little bit further on the sample - the area that has been selected. Is it coastal area? If so, need to be more careful as we all know that most of the people who lived there are categorized under \'lower middle income\". In this case, they were \"feel reluctant to insure their property due to premium and budget constraints (Aliagha et al., 2014). \r\nYou did mentioned \"Kota Bharu\" in the conclusion section so please explain it under data section. \r\n\r\nYou were also mentioned Protection Motivation Theory as to support your analysis (in page 5) but I cant see any discussion referring to that theory. You need more detail on the theory. \r\n\r\nThere are language and grammatical issue throughout that need careful checking.\r\n\r\nThe reference list is incomplete with reference in the text that are not in the list itself.\r\n(DID, 2007;2009)\r\n\r\n1. The author needs to add more literature in the study. No recent article is stated, only one.\r\n2. Repeatedly used the same literature in the study. Please avoid.\r\n3. The study needs to be precise, Kota Bharu only? Why used only 30 respondents? \r\n4. What is the motivation leads to this study? Please explain. ', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', 