(76, 'JEB.2019.07.01.015', 251, 'THE SUSTAINABILITY PERFORMANCE IN TELECOMMUNICATION FIRMS IN MALAYSIA', 'the sustainability performance in telecommunication firms in malaysia', 'Efficiency, firm performance, liquidity, leverage, firm size', 'This paper examines the influence of macroeconomic, external and internal risk factors towards the firm performance in terms of its profitability in Malaysian public and private firms of non-government telecommunication industry. A yearly basis data lies between 2007 and 2016, which contains a total number of 49 data observations with performed Pool Ordinary Least Square (POLS) and Random Effect econometric estimation models. There are two internal factors involved in this study such as liquidity (LIQ) and leverage (LEV) and a similar number of external factors such as size of a firm (SIZE) and gross domestic product (GDP). Some of the data are sourced from DataStream of UiTM and trading economy. Therefore, these variables are used to measure the overall performance of non-government telecommunication firms within 10 years? time. This study is motivated with the declining of telecommunication firms? performance in Malaysia due to a decreasing of return on asset (ROA). The finding suggests that leverage has a significant and negative relationship with the ROA. On the other hand, size has a significant and positive relationship with ROA. Therefore, the firms should not depend on GDP and liquidity to gain profit. In addition, the bigger the size of firm means the higher the total asset, thus improve the firm?s performance.', '', 5, 'ArticleWorkflow/ha-correction', '2019/asrulhery@gmail.com/submission_15590835685cedba30856fa6.07170535.docx', '2019-05-29 06:47:40', '2019-05-29 06:45:27', '2019-05-29 06:46:11', '2019-05-29 06:47:53', 91, 91, '2019/01258A/review_15590836595cedba8bf13f70.58505352.pdf', '', '2019-06-10 16:08:29', 0, '2019-06-11 21:09:04', 69, '2019-06-12 12:51:03', 'ME\'s Recommendation: Major Revision\r\n\r\nReviewers 