(80, 'JEB. 2019.07.01.011', 76, 'DETERMINANTS OF THE INTENTION TO PURCHASE FLOOD COVER: AN EMPIRICAL EVIDENCE FROM A FLOOD-PRONE AREA IN MALAYSIA', '', 'Flood Cover, Flood-Prone Area, Malaysia', 'In places where flood is a regular occurrence, it is apparent and widely known on the devastating effect of flood on property and human lives.  However, statistics by Persatuan Insurans Am Malaysia (PIAM) revealed that nearly 70% of homeowners in Malaysia do not have flood insurance. It is shown Thus, this paper aims to examine the relationship between perceived flood risks, flood damage experience and charity hazard on the purchase intention towards flood cover. 100 questionnaire managed to be collected from respondents living in a flood-prone area in Kota Bharu, Kelantan, Malaysia. The paper adopts a quantitative method of research design, which utilizes descriptive analysis, correlation analysis and regression analysis to analyses the raw data. The empirical results revealed that perceived flood risk, flood damage experience and charity hazard have a significant relationship with the purchase intention towards flood cover. The implication of this paper provides evidence of the importance of flood cover in the event of flood. ', '', 1, 'ArticleWorkflow/ha-correction', '2019/00283A/submission_15676551195d7084cf0d02a7.42707181.docx', '2019-09-05 11:48:27', '2019-09-05 11:44:35', '2019-09-05 11:45:26', '2019-09-05 12:04:11', 76, 76, '2019/00283A/review_15676553075d70858b412262.48946653.pdf', 'Assign internal and external', '2019-09-05 12:05:54', 0, '2019-09-15 11:41:36', 76, '2019-09-15 11:44:55', 'Panel 1\r\n\r\nThe article contributes to a new body of knowledge. Some improvement can be considered for this paper such as:\r\n\r\nLiterature review\r\nIt is quite short. Require more write-up to support the study.\r\n\r\nResearch methods\r\nSuggest informing where the data has been collected.\r\n\r\nOverall, this is a good paper and has the potential to be published.\r\n\r\nPan