(82, 'JEB.2019.08.01.001 (82)', 303, 'OWNERSHIP STRUCTURES AND FIRM PERFORMANCE IN NIGERIA: A CANONICAL CORRELATION ANALYSIS', '', 'Ownership Structure, Performance, Canonical Correlation, Tobin q, return on assets, return on equities, and earning per shares', 'This study examined the relationship between ownership structure and performance of listed non-financial firms in Nigeria. Secondary data on managerial ownership, ownership concentration, foreign ownership, institutional ownership, Tobin q, return on assets, return on equities, and earning per shares were collected from forty (40) sampled firms. The data were analyzed using canonical correlation and it was found that managerial and foreign ownership are the dominant ownership structures while Tobin q, EPS and ROA are the dominant performance measures. It was also found that ownership structures are positively correlated with firm performance. It was recommended that these firms should encourage foreign and managerial ownership by rewarding managers with shares in the firm. ', '', 4, 'ArticleWorkflow/da-review', '2019/uooba1009@gmail.com/submission_15678119105d72e946b33373.89308036.docx', '2019-09-09 09:27:51', '2019-09-07 07:16:55', '2019-09-07 07:18:41', '2019-09-09 09:28:19', 76, 76, '2019/00283A/review_15679924715d75aa97af70d1.94780083.pdf', 'Assign External and Internal', '2019-09-09 09:29:34', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', 0, 0, '', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', '', 0, '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, ''),
(83, 'JEB.2019.07.02.001', 76, 'INTERFACE EFFECTIVENESS (IE), CONFIDENCE IN SYSTEM (CS), EFFECTIVENESS OF USE (EU) AND DEMOGRAPHIC ELEMENTS TOWARDS INTENTION TO USE PUSTAKA NEGERI SARAWAK E-SERVICES \r\n(LIBRARY -SERVICES)\r\n', '', 'Intention to Use, e-services, online library, State Civil Servant', 'Malaysia government has been investing huge funding initiatives in building e-services for its national, state and municipal libraries.  This initiative is in support of the national aspiration for creating knowledge-based society.  From the perspective of the libraries, an online presence is pivotal in support to the increased rate of Internet usage among their stakeholders, academics and student alike, therefore the result of adopting electronic services has changed both the means of communicating with the users and nature of the service itself. The purpose of this research was to investigate the factors of Intention to Use libraries’ e-services specifically Pustaka Negeri Sarawak E-services by selected group of users; the State Civil Servant in Wisma Bapa Malaysia, Kuching Sarawak. Self-administered questionnaires was designed and distributed amongst State Civil Servant in Wisma Bapa Malaysia, Kuching Sarawak.  This research allows drawing the findings of three emerging factors of Intention to Use which are Interface Effectiveness (IU), Confidence in System (CS) and Effectiveness of Use (EU).  The most significant factors towards Intention to Use Pustaka Negeri Sarawak E-Services amongst State Civil Servant in Wisma Bapa Malaysia, Kuching Sarawak are Effectiveness of Use and Interface Effectiveness.  From the perspective of the user-centric approach, we identified the function of State Civil Servant in Wisma Bapa Malaysia Kuching Sarawak at increasing the Intention to Use Pustaka Negeri Sarawak E-Services by involving users’ in the designing phases of the libraries’ e-services. ', '', 5, 'ArticleWorkflow/ha-correction', '2019/00283A/submission_15707148715d9f34f741e604.17791215.docx', '2019-10-10 22:35:18', '2019-10-10 21:39:35', '2019-10-10 21:41:20', '2019-10-10 22:35:24', 76, 76, '2019/00283A/review_15707181175d9f41a5f155c3.18618256.pdf', '', '2019-10-11 16:10:15', 0, '2019-10-20 21:30:21', 76, '2019-10-21 15:38:14', 'Reviewer 1 Accept with minor revisions.\r\nReviewer 2 Ask for major revisions and allow to again be reviewed if re-submitted.\r\n\r\nReviewer 2 ask for 2nd review but her comments are too general. \r\n\r\nBoth reviewers commented on research problem which shown that the research problem is not clear and they agreed on reference section should be improved with citing the paper properly.\r\nthey also comments on methodology section but only reviewer 1 specific  the comments on model been used in this, reviewer 2\'s comments are general.\r\n\r\nI would suggest for accept with minor revision', 4, 4, 'Agree with the ME.', 55, '2019-10-23 08:50:09', 76, '2019-11-02 18:35:39', 'Panel 1:\r\n1. In your problem statement the author mentioned that people less use e-service provide by Pustaka Negara Sarawak. I believe this study should study/examine \'why\' the less use that service instead of intent to use? Intention to use did not reflect the issue raised by the author.\r\n\r\nMethodology:\r\nThe author claims that the study is based on model by Thong, Hong, & Tam, (2002). But where is the model? the model is missing in this paper.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nPlease check on how to cite paper.\r\n\r\nPage 3: Therefore, in addition to the current trend and use of social media as a platform for communicating which have been implemented in the work organization as a tool for communication with stakeholders and\r\ntheir employees (Hamad, Tbaishat, D., & Al-Fadel, M., 2016),\r\nPage 4, .... ease of use that behavioral expectation can be considered as one of the most influencing predictors exist for an individual future behavior (Davis F. D., 1989)\r\nInconsistencies in writing et al., et al. Please check\r\n\r\n\r\nPanel 2:\r\nThe title of the article required a revision. The problem statement did not clearly stated and the need of the study to focus on state civil servants as respondents should be mentioned. Perhaps the introduction and literature review sections should focus on the context perspective (broad) then followed by content (narrow/specific). The research methodology section also required more write-up and further explanations. Besides, the findings section should be well -presented with all statistical data and supported with previous findings/literature.\r\n\r\nMost of the citations quite out-of-date and suggested to author/s to search for latest literature. This article needs to be submitted for proof-read.\r\n\r\nDecision:\r\nAccept with minor revision', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', '', 0, '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, ''),
(84, '84', 76, 'A Proposed Framework for Researching Technopreneurial Intention among University Students in Malaysia', '', 'Entrepreneurial intention, Environmental factor, Students, Technology', 'Industrial revolution 4.0 (IR 4.0) is a new era which emphasizes on the use of information communication technology (ICT) and electronic applications in business operations. It requires young, innovative and ICT literate individuals. Malaysian government has put in a lot of efforts to develop entrepreneurial skills among the young generation especially university students. However, there are many challenges in developing young technology-based entrepreneurs or technopreneurs. For instance, Malaysia recorded low scores in a few entrepreneurial behaviors and attitudes identified by Global Entrepreneurial Monitor (GEM). Besides, not many Malaysians have established new businesses and the early stage entrepreneurship rate is still low and even decreasing. In addition, university students are showing low interest to become entrepreneurs during their tertiary education. The future of IR 4.0 is full of changes, unpredictable and very challenging. IR 4.0 would affect Malaysia’s vision and mission to develop competitive entrepreneurs and become a developed country. Thus, studies regarding technology-based entrepreneurship development in Malaysia is indeed needed. In the entrepreneurship literature, technological capability and psychological aspects such as individual entrepreneurial orientation (IEO) and entrepreneurial intention are insufficiently researched. Therefore, this research suggested a model to explain the direct and indirect influence of ICT self-efficacy and environmental factor on technopreneurial intention through IEO. In terms of the potential contributions of this research, it created a new model for exploring technopreneurial intention. In addition, it offered insights into policy implementation in developing competitive technopreneurial graduates, creating innovative individuals in technology fields and transforming Malaysia into a knowledge economy. It also identified the varieties of ICT capabilities which might be vital in developing revolutionary and entrepreneurial human capital. The framework can also be applied to facilitate, bolster and grow the participation of young generations in the technopreneurial activities.', '', 8, 'ArticleWorkflow/ba-pre-evaluate', '2019/00283A/submission_15707162225d9f3a3eeb2d82.48867402.docx', '2019-10-10 22:03:42', '2019-10-10 22:03:06', '2019-10-10 22:04:04', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', 0, 0, '', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', '', 0, '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, ''),
(85, 'JEB.2019.07.02.002 ', 76, 'The Provenance of Stress among Employees in Government Hospital in Malaysia', '', 'Stress, Job Enrichment, Facilities and Job Satisfaction', 'This study to identify the reasons for stress among employees in government hospital in Malaysia. The objective of this study is to measures the relationship between job enrichment, facilities and job satisfaction with provenance of stress and measure the predictor provenance of stress among employees in government hospital. Stress experienced at work can have adverse results for the prosperity of individual employees and association as entirety. This study is quantitative in nature and questionnaires distributed to collect information from respondents based on 150 sample size. The data obtained through questionnaires was analyzed and evaluated by statistical test correlation and regression. Most of the results show moderate and strong relationship on provenance of stress. Finally, limitation of study is also recognized and identified after the research is done. There are recommendations to the government hospitals and for future research to be conducted for better understanding in future.', '', 9, 'ArticleWorkflow/ra-reject', '2019/00283A/submission_15707164375d9f3b15745d68.00926213.docx', '2019-10-10 22:07:17', '2019-10-10 22:06:58', '2019-10-10 22:07:37', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', 0, 0, '', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, '2019-10-11 16:12:34', 76, 'Turnitin report is high, 30%. ', '', 0, '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, ''),
(86, 'JEB.2019.07.02.004', 76, 'Determinants of Household Debt in Malaysia ', '', 'Household debt, macroeconomic variable , multiple linear regression, ', 'The economist agreed that elevated household debt in Malaysia could add prolonged pressure to future economic growth and tarnish the financial stability. This study is using the time series data in identifying the household debt determinants in Malaysia. The Multiple Linear Regression (MLR) is used to see the relationship between the macroeconomic variables which are inflation rate, interest rate, saving level and unemployment towards the household debt in Malaysia. The findings for this study shown that, interest rate is the most significant variable followed by saving level and unemployment level. However, it is proven that inflation rate is insignificantly related with household debt in Malaysia. All the data are collected on monthly basis from Datastream which from January 2008 until June 2018 with 126 observations.', '', 4, 'ArticleWorkflow/ra-reject', '2019/00283A/submission_15707166225d9f3bceb07b33.18054295.docx', '2019-10-10 22:10:22', '2019-10-10 22:10:00', '2019-10-10 22:10:37', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', 0, 0, '', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, '2019-10-11 16:01:06', 76, 'Turnitin report is 82%. Very high', '', 0, '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, ''),
(87, '87', 76, 'Individual Entrepreneurs: What Makes Them Pay Their Loans?', '', 'Loan Repayment, Social Entrepreneurship, Family Business Influence', 'This study focuses on individual entrepreneurs and reasons for paying the loans they borrow as it may help individuals understand more about entrepreneurship. One of the advantages of entrepreneurship in Malaysia is it serves as a platform to secure loans from the Microfinance Institutions (MFIs) such as Tabung Ekonomi Kumpulan Usahawan Niaga (TEKUN). Individual entrepreneurs that borrow loans from MFIs might face a few risks such as default and bankruptcy if they are unable or fail to repay their loans. Loan default and bankruptcy are getting a serious attention in Malaysia since the number of loan repayments keeps increasing; however, the Microfinance Institutions (MFIs) in Malaysia still disburse new loans to borrowers.  Past literature revealed that many reasons can influence loan repayment. Therefore, this article is intended to review the determinants of loan repayment intention among entrepreneurs. The selected determinants that were found in the literature are attitude, religious belief, staff monitoring, self-efficacy, family business influence and experience', '', 4, 'ArticleWorkflow/ba-pre-evaluate', '2019/00283A/submission_15707167655d9f3c5dd875b4.06651983.docx', '2019-10-10 22:12:45', '2019-10-10 22:12:26', '2019-10-10 22:12:50', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', 0, 0, '', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', '', 0, '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00