(88, 'JEB.2019.07.02.006', 76, 'Factors Affecting Consumer’s Intention towards Purchasing Halal Collagen Beauty Drinks in Malaysia: a Structural Equation Modelling', '', ' Collagen Beauty Drinks; Halal; Muslim; Purchase Intention; Women Consumers.', 'This study attempted to highlight the relationship between three factors; attitude, subjective norms, and knowledge of consumers towards their intention to purchase Halal collagen beauty drink products. There is an increasing trend of collagen beauty drink products consumption among women in Malaysia in recent years. As a Muslim nation, the sources of collagen which are mainly derived from animal parts have become a major concern for Muslim consumers, especially its Halal status. In addition, the target respondents were females because they are beauty conscious and willing to spend a large amount to buy several ranges of collagen beauty drink products being offered in the market. The sample of the study consisted of 380 Muslim female customers at the Klang Valley areas. Data were collected through self- administered questionnaires by using a two-stages sampling technique. Structural Equation Model (SEM) was used to develop and test the conceptual model. The results show that attitude, knowledge and subjective norms have significant relationship with consumer purchase intention behaviour towards collagen beauty drink products', '', 1, 'ArticleWorkflow/ha-correction', '2019/00283A/submission_15707169455d9f3d11bb3063.98122084.docx', '2019-10-20 21:25:07', '2019-10-10 22:15:25', '2019-10-10 22:15:48', '2019-10-20 21:25:23', 76, 76, '2019/00283A/review_15715779075dac6033331ca5.19093606.pdf', 'Assign two reviewer, internal n external', '2019-10-20 21:28:01', 0, '2019-10-30 16:03:12', 76, '2019-10-30 16:06:02', 'Panel 1:  Accept with minor revision  \r\nComment is too general which is The background of study or related issues was clearly discussed. However, the researcher need to look into the citation formatting.\r\n\r\nPanel 2: Accept with minor revision\r\nComments are specific:\r\n\r\nThis is very interesting topic especially on purchasing halal products and in fact the way the author(s) present her/his study is well written. However, there are a few questions require author(s) further justification\r\n\r\n1. What makes you to investigate this \'health\' product? What is collagen?\r\n2.In introduction, the author (s) mentioning a few names of collagen drink such as local brand like Qu Putih, Gluta Collagen Berry, Kcolly, Babies Blink Collagen. As these brand are really halal? As previously these brands are having controversy of consist of prohibition ingredient like mercury etc.\r\n3. Where is your hypotheses? There should be hypotheses stated in your paper before you run the analysis.\r\n4. In methodology section, you mentioned \"The subjects for this study were young generation of Muslim women consumers in the Lembah Klang area who represented a majority of collagen users in Malaysia\". Is it true?How and where did you get this fact?\r\n5.\"The women from Gen-Y population ranged between 20 - 45 years old\". Who said this?\r\n6. How do you approach the respondent and to identify the correct respondent to answer your survey?\r\n7.\" Each observation measures one or more properties (such as weight, location, colour) of observable bodies\r\ndistinguished as independent objects or individuals. In survey sampling, weights can be applied to the data to adjust for the sample design, particularly stratified sampling. Results from probability theory and statistical theory are employed to guide the practice\" What do you mean by this?\r\n8. It is good if authors can show us the demographic profile of the respondent so that we can see in what age does really consume for collagen product.\r\n9. Why you study intention? Your respondent is someone who purchased and consumed collagen product. Why dont you study what factor affecting them to purchase collagen product.\r\n9. What software you used ? It is SmartPLS or AMOS? I think its AMOS. If you used AMOS, did your data normally distribute? Any justification is required for this.\r\n10. Discussion section is not well discuss.\r\n\r\nI suggest for minor correction', 4, 4, 'Acceptable with minor correction.', 55, '2019-10-31 08:22:43', 76, '2019-11-02 18:34:16', 'Panel 1: Accept with minor revision\r\nPanel 2:\r\nThis is very interesting topic especially on purchasing halal products and in fact the way the author(s) present her/his study is well written. However, there are a few questions require author(s) further justification\r\n\r\n1. What makes you to investigate this \'health\' product? What is collagen?\r\n2.In introduction, the author (s) mentioning a few names of collagen drink such as local brand like Qu Putih, Gluta Collagen Berry, Kcolly, Babies Blink Collagen. As these brand are really halal? As previously these brands are having controversy of consist of prohibition ingredient like mercury etc.\r\n3. Where is your hypotheses? There should be hypotheses stated in your paper before you run the analysis.\r\n4. In methodology section, you mentioned \"The subjects for this study were young generation of Muslim women consumers in the Lembah Klang area who represented a majority of collagen users in Malaysia\". Is it true?How and where did you get this fact?\r\n5.\"The women from Gen-Y population ranged between 20 - 45 years old\". Who said this?\r\n6. How do you approach the respondent and to identify the correct respondent to answer your survey?\r\n7.\" Each observation measures one or more properties (such as weight, location, colour) of observable bodies\r\ndistinguished as independent objects or individuals. In survey sampling, weights can be applied to the data to adjust for the sample design, particularly stratified sampling. Results from probability theory and statistical theory are employed to guide the practice\" What do you mean by this?\r\n8. It is good if authors can show us the demographic profile of the respondent so that we can see in what age does really consume for collagen product.\r\n9. Why you study intention? Your respondent is someone who purchased and consumed collagen product. Why dont you study what factor affecting them to purchase collagen product.\r\n9. What software you used ? It is SmartPLS or AMOS? I think its AMOS. If you used AMOS, did your data normally distribute? Any justification is required for this.\r\n10. Discussion section is not well discuss.\r\n\r\nDecision:\r\nAccept with minor revisions.', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', '', 0, '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, ''),
(89, 'JEB.2019.07.02.007', 308, 'The Provenance of Stress among Employees in Government Hospital in Malaysia', '', 'Stress, Job Enrichment, Facilities and Job Satisfaction', 'This study to identify the reasons for stress between employees in government hospital in Malaysia. The objective of this research is to measures the association between job enrichment, facilities and job satisfaction with provenance of stress and measure the predictor provenance of stress among employees in government hospital. Stress experienced at work can have adverse results for the prosperity of individual employees and association as entirety. This study is quantitative in nature and questionnaires distributed to gather information from respondents based on 150 sample size. The data obtained through questionnaires was analyzed and evaluated by statistical test correlation and regression. Most of the results show moderate and strong relationship on provenance of stress. Finally, limitation of study is also recognized and identified after the research is done. There are recommendations to the government hospitals and for future research to be conducted for better understanding in future.', '', 5, 'ArticleWorkflow/da-review', '2019/noorainnordin@uitm.edu.my/submission_15725814495dbbb0496c0bb4.41919451.docx', '2019-11-02 18:51:20', '2019-11-01 12:08:25', '2019-11-01 12:11:09', '2019-11-02 18:51:27', 76, 76, '2019/00283A/review_15726918805dbd5fa8b226a8.07298201.pdf', '', '2019-11-02 18:54:06', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', 0, 0, '', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, '', '', 0, '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '00