(24, 66, 4, 77, 20, 3, 4, 4, 1, 4, 4, 4, 2, 2, 2, 4, 3, 'Abstract\r\n•	Should be precise and explained important findings. The last sentence in abstract section is unclear and not abstract-suitable.\r\n\r\nIntroduction.\r\n•	The definition of Organizational Climate (OC) and Organizational Citizenship Behavior (OCB) should be discussed early in this section in order to allow readers understand the content of the paper.\r\n•	The used of abbreviated need to be corrected. The ‘OCB’ abbreviation only appear at page 3 while Organizational Citizenship Behavior is written a number of times beginning from page 1. This applies to other abbreviations used in this paper (EI, LMX, ECL and others)\r\n•	The flow of writing makes it is difficult to understand because in many parts, the sentences and paragraph are not linked to previous sentence.\r\n\r\nStudy objectives\r\n•	Not clear\r\n\r\n Theories Foundations\r\n•	The flow of writing makes it is difficult to understand because in many parts, the sentences and paragraph are not linked to previous sentence.\r\n•	Para 2, line 4 needs citation.\r\n•	How is social intelligence and emotional intelligence similar (Para 2, line 1).\r\n•	Para 5, Line 1, LMX is not written full as this is the first time abbreviation is used.\r\n•	Para 7 – to reconsider if the para is suitable for theories foundations’ section.\r\n\r\nLiterature Review\r\n•	Malaysian Banking Industry – need to include previous literature of Malaysian Banking Industry studies with regard to OCB, OC. For now, the written facts are not Lit Review.\r\n•	Lit Review supposed to discussed previous method/operations/ findings of related study. This paper however only provides the definitions of its variables. Non- explained how previous studies used items included in the stated framework. Therefore, how the framework is generated for this study currently have weak foundation.\r\n•	How each variable measured is previous studies are not explained?\r\n\r\nFramework development and Hypotheses\r\n•	Refer to Literature Review, bullet number 2\r\n•	Framework does not include arrow direction of relationship\r\n•	Typo for H7\r\n\r\nMethodology\r\n•	Suggestion to use table in presenting facts of measurement, EI, LMX, OC, OCB\r\n•	what is SEA, OEA, ROE, UOE, OCBI, OCBO\r\nFindings and Analysis\r\n•	Table 2 – item that shows high correlation need to be justified.\r\n\r\nDiscussion\r\n•	The author used this section to do a written version of results that are already presented using tables in previous section. Results is however not discussed in this section as claimed by the subtitle.\r\n\r\nConclusion\r\n•	This is a section where summary of important findings should be written.\r\n\r\nLimitation and Future Research\r\n•	What type of bank currently the study used as sample? It is not mentioned in sampling procedure.\r\n\r\nAcknowledgement\r\n•	AAMJ? ?\r\n', '2019/00185A/reviewed_15586871195ce7ad8f2a0943.42104830.docx', '2019-05-24 16:38:39', '2019-05-20 22:41:03', '2019-05-24 16:39:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
