(59, 69, 1, 264, 20, 4, 5, 4, 4, 4, 5, 5, 5, 5, 4, 3, 3, '1. Abstract \r\n-the term of \"TPB model\" should be in full spelling (Theory of Perceived Behaviour Model).\r\n- the contribution/significant of the study is recommended to be added in the abstract.\r\n\r\n2. Introduction\r\n - several of the statements did not have citations.\r\n-  recommended to explain the content of the study, which is the  intention to adopt technology, followed by context which is the which is electric vehicles (EVs) with arguments on related studies been done by scholars, \r\n- spelling error \'overview of transportation in Jordan\'\r\n- it also should highlight the problem statement of this study.\r\n\r\n3. The literature review slightly not sufficient as it only discussed on the TPB model. \r\n\r\n4. Methodology\r\n-Paragraph 1 is recommended to rewrite. For example para 1, line 3 - \" As the study was aimed to examine the factors that influence the EVs behavioral intentions in Jordan\". The statement was incomplete and unclear as it also contradicted with objective mentioned in the abstract (abstract, line 4).\r\n- recommended to include how the sampling were selected (sampling technique)\r\n\r\n5. Result\r\n- a few of the tables presented split into another page. \r\n\r\n6. Discussion\r\n- Para 1, line 1-10 - the statement is repetitive with the abstract (line 1-10).\r\n- recommended to rewrite this section. \r\n\r\nThe article is highly recommended to submit to proof reader before submission. \r\n\r\n\r\n                           -', '', '2019-06-11 12:49:24', '2019-05-29 12:41:06', '2019-06-11 13:36:50', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
