(122, 80, 1, 76, 20, 4, 5, 5, 3, 4, 2, 4, 3, 4, 4, 3, 4, 'LR- I suggest the author could explain more on this section as thi section is crucial in supporting all variables involved in this study.\r\nWhat you mean by purchase intention? You want to study people intention to buy flood insurance?\r\nhypotheses are missing. \r\n\r\nMethodology\r\nWhere is the section for sampling and population? How you approach the respondent.?How you conduct the survey? face to face? or administrated questionaire?\r\nWhere and how do you get the respondent?\r\nThe source of the questionaire is missing and please put details the list of questions involved in this study\r\nHave this study gone for etthic community for approval? This study is dealing with the respondent who had experience in \' hard flood\'. It can affect the psyhcology of the respondent.\r\n\r\nDiscussion is well discussed but i want to see how this is aligned with Protection MotivationTheory. ', '', '2019-09-06 12:16:21', '2019-09-06 12:15:03', '2019-09-06 13:17:18', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(123, 81, 4, 70, 20, 3, 3, 3, 3, 4, 2, 3, 3, 4, 4, 2, 3, '1. The paper require proofreading for conciseness and grammatical correctness. \r\n2. Abbreviations used are confusing readers and make reading difficult (exception to ROA and ROE)\r\n3. Mukhopadhyay (1986) is very old data to rely on for current situation, unless supported with current study about the same issue. \r\n4. The discussions -What is (are) the author\'s opinion (s) regarding the findings of the study? How the findings relate to the banks in the study?', '', '2019-09-08 09:35:41', '2019-09-06 13:19:31', '2019-09-23 08:38:37', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
