(129, 83, 1, 76, 20, 3, 4, 3, 3, 2, 4, 3, 3, 3, 3, 2, 4, '1. In your problem statement the author mentioned that people less use e-service provide by Pustaka Negara Sarawak. I believe this study should study/examine \'why\' the less use that service instead of intent to use? Intention to use did not reflect the issue raised by the author.\r\n\r\nMethodology:\r\nThe author claims that the study is based on model by Thong, Hong, & Tam, (2002). But where is the model? the model is missing in this paper.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nPlease check on how to cite paper.\r\n\r\nPage 3: Therefore, in addition to the current trend and use of social media as a platform for communicating which have been implemented in the work organization as a tool for communication with stakeholders and\r\ntheir employees (Hamad, Tbaishat, D., & Al-Fadel, M., 2016),\r\n Page 4, .... ease of use that behavioral expectation can be considered as one of the most influencing predictors exist for an individual future behavior (Davis F. D., 1989)\r\nInconsistencies in writing et al., et al. Please check\r\n', '', '2019-10-17 12:34:28', '2019-10-11 16:10:15', '2019-10-20 21:10:17', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(130, 83, 1, 264, 20, 3, 3, 3, 2, 4, 3, 4, 4, 3, 4, 2, 2, 'The title of the article required a revision. The problem statement did not clearly stated and the need of the study to focus on state civil servants as respondents should be mentioned. Perhaps the introduction and literature review sections should focus on the context perspective (broad) then followed by content (narrow/specific). The research methodology section also required more write-up and further explanations.  Besides, the findings section should be well -presented with all statistical data and supported with previous findings/literature. \r\n\r\nMost of the citations quite out-of-date and suggested to author/s to search for latest literature. This article needs to be submitted for proof-read.\r\n', '', '2019-10-14 12:33:31', '2019-10-11 16:10:15', '2019-10-14 12:56:44', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(131, 88, 1, 123, 20, 4, 4, 4, 4, 3, 4, 4, 4, 4, 4, 4, 4, 'The background of study or related issues  was clearly discussed. However, the researcher need to look into the citation formatting. ', '', '2019-10-20 22:29:48', '2019-10-20 21:28:01', '2019-10-22 14:51:41', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
